open_spaces_details.open_space_type: Provision for children and young people

description: Demolition of the existing building and erection of four blocks ranging from three to eleven storeys to provide 333 residential units and commercial space with associated car and cycle parking, landscaping, amenity space and ancillary development
decision_conditions: Condition : 1 - The development hereby permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Condition : 2 - The proposed development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the proposals contained in the application and the plans submitted (MTW-PTE-ZZ-ZZ-DR- A-10300 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-ZZ-DR- A-10301 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-ZZ-DR- A-10000 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-ZZ-DR- A-10001 P01, MTW-PTE-AD-01-DR-A-10101 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-02-DR-A-10102 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-03-DR-A-10103 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-04-DR-A-10104 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-05-DR-A-10105 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-06-DR-A-10106 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-07-DR-A-10107 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-08-DR-A-10108 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-09-DR-A-10109 C01, MTW-PTE-AD-10-DR-A-10110 C01, MTW, PTE-BC-02-DR- A-10102 C01, MTW-PTE-BC-03-DR- A-10103 C01, MTW-PTE-BC-04-DR- A-10104 C01, MTW-PTE-BC-05-DR- A-10105 C01, MTW-PTE-BC-06-DR- A-10106 C01, MTW-PTE-BC-RF-DR- A-10107 C01, MTW-PTE-C-XX-DR-A- 10400 C01, MTW-PTE-EFG-01-DR-A-10101 C01, MTW-PTE-EFG-02-DR-A-10102 C01, MTW-PTE-EFG-03-DR-A-10103 C01, MTW-PTE-EFG-04-DR-A-10104 C01, MTW-PTE-EFG-05-DR-A-10105 C01, MTW-PTE-EFG-06-DR-A-10106 C01, MTW-PTE-HJ-01-DR-A-10101 C01, MTW-PTE-HJ-02-DR-A-10102 C01, MTW-PTE-HJ-03-DR-A-10103 C01, MTW-PTE-HJ-04-DR-A-10104 C01, MTW-PTE-HJ-05-DR-A-10105 C01, MTW-PTE-HJ-06-DR-A-10106 C01, MTW-PTE-HJ-RF-DR-A-10107 C01, MTW-PTE-H-XX-DR-A-10400 C01, MTW-PTE-H-XX-DR-A-10401 C01, MTW-PTE-J-XX-DR-A-10400 C01, MTW-PTE-M-XX-DR-A-10400 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-00-DR-A-10100 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-01-DR-A-10101 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-02-DR-A-10002 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-02-DR-A-10102 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-03-DR-A-10003 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-03-DR- A-10103 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-04-DR- A-10004 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-05-DR- A-10005 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-06-DR- A-10006 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-XX-DR- A-10307 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-XX-DR- A-10308 C01, MTW-PTE-ZZ-ZZ-DR- A-10002 C01: Received 04/04/2022.
MTW-PTE-ZZ-00-DR-A-10000 C03, MTW-PTE-ZZ-01-DR-A-10001 C02, MTW-PTE-ZZ-07-DR- A-10007 C02, MTW-PTE-ZZ-08-DR- A-10008 C02, MTW-PTE-ZZ-09-DR- A-10009 C02, MTW-PTE-ZZ-10-DR- A-10010 C02, MTW-PTE-ZZ-RF-DR- A-10011 C02, MTW-PTE-ZZ-ZZ-DR- A-10003 C03, MTW-PTE-AD-01-DR-A-10100 C02, MTW-PTE-AD-RF-DR- A-10111 C02, MT

Condition : 3 - During the course of the development:
a. Works shall be carried out in accordance with the Geotechnical and Geoenvironmental Interpretative Report and Remediation Strategy hereby approved at all times.
b. The Local Planning Authority shall be notified immediately if additional contamination is discovered during the course of the development. A competent person shall assess any such additional contamination, and shall submit appropriate amendments to the scheme for decontamination in writing to the Local Planning Authority for approval before any work on that aspect of development continues.
Before the development is first brought into use:
c. The agreed scheme for decontamination referred to in the Geotechnical and Geoenvironmental Interpretative Report and Remediation Strategy hereby approved, including any amendments approved under part b of this condition, shall be fully implemented and a written validation (closure) report shall be submitted to, and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to first use of each block.

Condition : 4 - No demolition or development below ground level shall take place until a stage 1 written scheme of investigation (WSI) has been submitted to and approved by the local planning authority in writing. For land that is included within the WSI, no demolition or development shall take place other than in accordance with the agreed WSI, and the programme and methodology of site evaluation and the nomination of a competent person(s) or organisation to undertake the agreed works.
If heritage assets of archaeological interest are identified by the stage 1 WSI, then for those parts of the site which have archaeological interest a stage 2 WSI shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority in writing. For land that is included within the stage 2 WSI, no demolition/development shall take place other than in accordance with the agreed stage 2 WSI which shall include:
A. The statement of significance and research objectives, the programme and methodology of site investigation and recording and the nomination of a competent person(s) or organisation to undertake the agreed works
B. Details of a programme for delivering related positive public benefits
C. The programme for post-investigation assessment and subsequent analysis, publication & dissemination and deposition of resulting material. This part of the condition shall not be discharged until these elements have been fulfilled in accordance with the programme set out in the stage 2 WSI.

Condition : 5 - Prior to the commencement of superstructure works, an updated air quality assessment shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, to provide pollutant levels at the proposed sensitive receptors within the proposed development red line boundary (for all floors and facades). Should the modelled concentrations at proposed sensitive receptors be equal or higher than 36 ?g/m3, adequate mitigation measures should be incorporated into the scheme. Works shall be carried out in accordance with the agreed details and retained permanently thereafter.

Condition : 6 - Noise levels from construction works at nearby existing and proposed residential receptors shall not exceed the following construction noise criteria (as outlined in guidance contained within BS 5228:2009 + A1:2014: Noise):
Daytime works will not exceed 75 dB LAeq,T at the worst-affected residential property during the following time periods:
-Monday to Friday (08:00 ? 18:00 hours)
-Saturday (08:00 to 13:00 hours)
Works shall not take place outside of the standard hours, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Condition : 7 - a. The cumulative noise from any fixed external plant associated with the scheme shall not exceed levels more than 10 dB below representative background (LA90) levels at free field locations representing facades of nearby existing and proposed dwellings. Noise levels shall be assessed by measurement or calculation based on the guidance presented within BS4142: 2014+A1:2019 or subsequent versions of this guidance.
b. Upon installation of the proposed fixed plant and any associated mitigation, an acoustic commissioning survey shall be undertaken. The cumulative measured or calculated Rating Level of noise emitted from all mechanical services plant including heating, ventilation and air conditioning (HVAC) shall be 10dB(A) below the existing background noise level, at all times that the mechanical system etc operates. The measured or calculated noise levels shall be determined at the boundary of the nearest ground floor noise sensitive premises or 1 metre from the fa?ade of the nearest first floor (or higher) noise sensitive premises, and in accordance with the latest revision of British Standard 4142. Prior to first occupation of the development, the results of the acoustic commissioning survey shall be submitted to and agreed in writing with the Local Planning Authority.

Condition : 9 - a. Works shall be carried out in accordance with the details set out in the Noise Impact Assessment Ref: 21-8038, NIA Rev C dated 30 March 2022 and Syntegra Consulting Response to the London Borough of Hounslow dated 01 July 2022.
b. Notwithstanding the approved details, prior to the development being first occupied, details of the glazing to be used shall be submitted to and agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority to confirm that maximum noise levels permitted within the dwellings shall not exceed:
-Living Rooms = NR30 during daytime (07:00 - 23:00)
-Bedroom = NR25 during daytime (07:00 - 23:00)
-Bedroom = NR20 during night-time (23:00 - 07:00)
-Bedroom = LAmax noise levels within bedrooms do not exceed 45 dB LAmax more than 10 to 15 times during night-time (23:00 - 07:00)
-All occupiers should have access to amenity spaces where noise levels do not exceed 50dB LAeq,16hours
-Bedrooms with a direct line of sight to MSO Boatyard to have a minimum glazing performance of 44dB Rw
-Living rooms with a direct line of sight to MSO Boatyard to have a minimum glazing performance of 39dB Rw
Works shall be carried out in accordance with the agreed details and retained permanently thereafter.
c. Prior to first occupation of the dwellings, the results of internal ambient noise level validation testing shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority to demonstrate that the criteria outlined within part a of this condition has met within the sensitive rooms.

Condition : 10 - Prior to the commencement of superstructure works, details shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority of the sound insulation of the floor/ ceiling/ walls separating the residential to residential parts of the premises. Details shall demonstrate that the sound insulation value DnT,w [and L'nT,w] is enhanced by at least 5dB above the maximum recommended Building Regulations value, for the floor/ceiling /wall structures separating different types of rooms/ uses in adjoining dwellings, namely [living rooms/ bathrooms/ kitchens above or adjoining bedrooms of separate dwellings].
The approved details shall be implemented before the development is first occupied and retained permanently thereafter. Where necessary, additional mitigation measures shall be implemented achieve the criteria of BS8233:2014 within the dwellings/noise sensitive premises. Approved details shall be implemented prior to occupation of the development and thereafter be permanently retained.

Condition : 11 - No works shall commence within 16 metres of the river wall/flood defence and any supporting buried elements with the exception of demolition works using hand tools until a Risk Assessment and Method Statement including a loading plan for any works within 16 metres of the river wall/flood defence is submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, in consultation with the Canal & River Trust and Environment Agency. The statement shall include an assessment of the existing waterway wall and railings and outline the necessary repairs or mitigation measures that are required, and include details of any buried support structures such as anchor blocks and tie rods. This scheme needs to be in line with the proposed strategy outlined in the second issue of the document titled 'River Wall Asset Management Strategy' (ref: FNH444-RP-001, dated 25.07.2022). Works shall comply with the Canal & River Trust "Code of Practice for Works affecting the Canal & River Trust".

Condition : 12 - A scheme to replace the river wall/ flood defence shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, in consultation with the Environment Agency before the construction of any foundations commence. This scheme needs to be in line with the proposed strategy outlined in the Second Issue of the document titled ?River Wall Asset Management Strategy? (ref: FNH444-RP-001, dated 25.07.2022). The scheme shall be supported by structural and stability calculations to achieve a life expectancy of the river wall of no less than 100 years without needing a major intervention and demonstrating the ability to raise the wall crest in the future for sea level rise without undue cost and difficulty in line with the Thames Estuary TE2100 plan. The development shall then only proceed in accordance with the approved scheme and shall be maintained as such thereafter.

Condition : 13 - Details of measures to minimise overlooking and increase the perception of privacy for all units in Blocks J that have habitable room windows within 18 metres of opposing habitable rooms windows in neighbouring properties shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to any works above ground. The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the approved details and retained as such permanently thereafter.

Condition : 14 - a. Prior to commencement of groundworks (excluding site investigations and demolition), the applicant must submit a final detailed drainage design including drawings, supporting calculations and updated SuDS Proforma to the Local Planning Authority to be approved in writing, in consultation with the Lead Local Flood Authority, aligned with the Drainage Strategy Report (dated July 2022) and associated drawings. All proposed SuDS features and the total site area should be incorporated into the calculations. It should be demonstrated that on-site flow as a result of the 1 in 100 year event with a climate change consideration must be suitably managed, with exceedance flows directed away from buildings. A detailed management plan confirming routine maintenance tasks for all drainage components must also be submitted to demonstrate how the drainage system is to be maintained for the lifetime of the development. Consent from the Canal and River Trust for the proposed discharge connection must be provided.
b. No building hereby permitted shall be occupied until evidence (photographs and installation contracts) is submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, to demonstrate that the sustainable drainage scheme for the site has been completed in accordance with the details approved under part a of this condition. The sustainable drainage scheme shall be managed and maintained permanently thereafter in accordance with the agreed management and maintenance plan for all of the proposed drainage components.

Condition : 15 - No piling shall take place until a Piling Method Statement (detailing the depth and type of piling to be undertaken and the methodology by which such piling will be carried out, including measures to prevent and minimise the potential for damage to subsurface sewerage infrastructure, and the programme for the works) has been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority in consultation with Thames Water. Any piling must be undertaken in accordance with the terms of the approved piling method statement.

Condition : 16 - No construction shall take place within 5 metres of the water main. Prior to commencement of below ground works, information detailing how the developer intends to divert the asset / align the development, so as to prevent the potential for damage to subsurface potable water infrastructure, must be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority in consultation with Thames Water. Any construction must be undertaken in accordance with the terms of the approved information. Unrestricted access must be available at all times for the maintenance and repair of the asset during and after the construction works.

Condition : 17 - Prior to first occupation of the development, confirmation shall be provided that either: all water network upgrades required to accommodate the additional demand to serve the development have been completed; or - a development and infrastructure phasing plan has been agreed with Thames Water to allow development to be occupied. Where a development and infrastructure phasing plan is agreed no occupation of the development shall take place other than in accordance with the agreed development and infrastructure phasing plan.

Condition : 18 - Prior to first occupation of the development, an amended Fire Statement shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, in consultation with the Health and Safety Executive.

Condition : 19 - A minimum of 10% of the total dwellings shall be ?Wheelchair User Dwellings? built to Building Regulations M4(3) standard shall be provided as identified on the Schedule of Accommodation ? Residential Rev P03 dated 26.08.2022. All other dwellings shall be designed so that they meet building regulation M4 (2) 'accessible and adaptable dwellings'.
Condition : 20 - The Commercial units hereby permitted shall not be open to customers other than between 7:00am and 22:00pm Mondays to Saturday and 10:00am ? 18:00pm on Sundays.

Condition : 21 - Commercial Units 3, 4, 5, 6 and 7 hereby approved shall only be used as Use Class E(g) and for no other purposes in the wider Use Class E of the Schedule to the Town and Country Planning (Use Classes) Order 1987 (as amended), or in any provision equivalent to that Class in any statutory instrument revoking and re-enacting that Order with or without modification.

Condition : 22 - Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) (or any order revoking or re-enacting that order) no change of use under Part 3 Class MA shall be carried out, or enlargement of the premises or any additional structures/buildings within the curtilage of the site shall be carried out without the prior written consent of the Local Planning Authority.

Condition : 23 - No development (except demolition, archaeological investigations, ground condition investigations and intrusive site surveys and other enabling works: site clearance; soil storage; remedial works in respect of any contamination or any other adverse ground conditions; erection of any temporary means of enclosure and land raising) shall take place until details (including product specifications) and samples of all facing materials are submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The samples and details shall include:
i. brick/stonework (including brick/stone and mortar onsite sample panel min. 2m x 2m, in line with the Montgomery?s Wharf Brentford Brickwork Intent submitted 21/07/2022);
ii. cladding materials (including system specifications/details and on-site samples (where relevant);
iii. window treatment (including sections/reveals and samples); and
iv. privacy measures, (including obscure glazing details)
v. balustrading treatment (details/sections/materials for each balcony type)
vi. details of the amended terrace and boundary treatment for unit 31
vii. any other materials/details to be used.
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.

Condition : 25 - Prior to the first occupation, a Parking Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The plan shall include details of how the spaces will be allocated, how misuse will be managed, measures to ensure that the delivery and servicing area is kept free for its intended purpose, and include details of both active and passive EV charging provisions as required by the London Plan. The site shall thereafter operate in accordance with the approved details.

Condition : 26 - Prior to first occupation of the development, full details (including manufacturer?s specifications) of all cycle stands for the occupants of, and visitors to, the development shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The approved facilities shall be fully implemented and made available for use before any part of the development is first occupied and thereafter retained for use at all times without obstruction.

Condition : 27 - Prior to first occupation of the development, an updated Delivery and Servicing Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details shall accord with current guidance such as that issued by Transport for London and shall include measures required to ensure sufficient arrangements, physical as well as managerial, for the servicing, including emergency vehicle access, including refuse collection, of all aspects of the development, the timing of hours for deliveries by motor vehicles and a timetable for implementation. The Plan shall be carried out as approved. The approved measures shall be implemented before the first occupation of the development hereby permitted and shall be so maintained for the life of the development.

Condition : 28 - a.) The development hereby permitted shall be implemented in accordance with the hereby approved Energy Statement dated March 2022 and the Addendum Letter received 23/08/2022.
b.) Prior to the first occupation of each building or first use of the commercial space, evidence (e.g. photographs, installation contracts and As-Built certificates under the Standard Assessment Procedure/National Calculation Method) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority to show that the development has been constructed in accordance with the approved Energy Statement to achieve a site-wise carbon reduction in emissions of 66% on Part L Building Regulations.
c.) Upon final commencement of operation of any low and zero carbon technologies, suitable devices for the monitoring of the low and zero carbon technologies shall have been installed, and the monitored data shall be submitted automatically to a monitoring web-platform at daily intervals for a period of three years from the point of full operation.

Condition : 29 - Prior to the commencement of development (except demolition, archaeological investigations, ground condition investigations and intrusive site surveys and other enabling works: site clearance; soil storage; remedial works in respect of any contamination or any other adverse ground conditions; erection of any temporary means of enclosure and land raising), evidence shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority to show that the development has made sufficient provisions to enable the connection to a feasible district heating network in the future including a safeguarded pipe route for future connection at the site boundary. The development shall be constructed and completed in accordance with the agreed details.

Condition : 30 - Prior to the first occupation of flats hereby approved, evidence (schedule of fittings and manufactures literature) shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority to demonstrate that the development would achieve the internal 105 litres per person per day target.

Condition : 31 - The development shall not be occupied until evidence (e.g. photographs and copies of installation contracts) has been submitted to the Local Planning Authority to demonstrate that the development has been carried out in accordance with the following sustainable sourcing of materials requirements:
- At least three of the key elements of the building envelope (external walls, windows roof, upper floor slabs, internal walls, floor finishes/coverings) are to achieve a rating of A+ to D in the Building Research Establishment (BRE) The Green Guide of specification.
- At least 50% of timber and timber products are to be sourced from accredited Forest Stewardship Council (FSC) or Programme for the Endorsement of Forestry Certification (PEFC) scheme.
- No construction or insulation materials are to be used which would release toxins into the internal and external environment, including those that deplete stratospheric ozone.

Condition : 32 - Prior to the commencement of above ground works on each block, a design stage BREEAM Retail New Construction Shell only Design Stage certificate and summary score sheet (or such equivalent standard that replaces this) must be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority to show that an ?Excellent? (minimum score 70%) rating shall be achieved.

Condition : 33 - Within six months of first occupation of the commercial units, a post-construction stage BREEAM Retail New Construction Shell only Design Stage certificate and summary score sheet (or such equivalent standard that replaces this) must be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority to show that an ?Excellent? (minimum score 70%) rating has been achieved.

Condition : 34 - Prior to the first occupation of each building the post-construction tab of the GLA?s whole life carbon assessment template should be completed accurately and in its entirety in line with the GLA?s Whole Life Carbon Assessment Guidance. The post-construction assessment should provide an update of the information submitted at planning submission stage, including the whole life carbon emission figures for all life-cycle modules based on the actual materials, products and systems used. This should be submitted to the GLA at: ZeroCarbonPlanning@london.gov.uk, along with any supporting evidence as per the guidance. Confirmation of submission to the GLA shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Condition : 35 - Prior to the first occupation of each building, a Post Completion Report setting out the predicted and actual performance against all numerical targets in the relevant Circular Economy Statement shall be submitted to the GLA at: CircularEconomyLPG@london.gov.uk, along with any supporting evidence as per the GLA?s Circular Economy Statement Guidance. The Post Completion Report shall provide updated versions of Tables 1 and 2 of the Circular Economy Statement, the Recycling and Waste Reporting form and Bill of Materials. Confirmation of submission to the GLA shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority.

Condition : 36 - The development shall achieve 'Secured by Design' accreditation awarded by the Design-Out Crime Officer from the Metropolitan Police Service on behalf of the Association of Chief Police Officers (ACPO). Prior to first occupation of the dwellings, evidence of the accreditation achieved shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

Condition : 38 - Prior to the commencement of the development (except demolition, archaeological investigations, ground condition investigations and intrusive site surveys and other enabling works: site clearance; soil storage; remedial works in respect of any contamination or any other adverse ground conditions; erection of any temporary means of enclosure and land raising), a Biodiversity Enhancement Strategy, incorporating the recommendations of the Ecological Appraisal Report dated 03/03/2022, and shall details the type and position of bird and bat boxes, log piles, green roof meadow, rain gardens and other habitats of importance to increase species diversity, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The strategy shall also include an ecological management and monitoring plan including long- term design objectives, management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all landscaped areas (except privately owned domestic gardens). The approved Biodiversity Enhancement Strategy shall be implemented prior to the first occupation of the development. Any enhancement measures shall be maintained throughout the lifetime of the development.

Condition : 39 - All Non-road Mobile Machinery (NRMM) used during the course of the development that is within the scope of the GLA ?Control of Dust and Emissions during Construction and Demolition? Supplementary Planning Guidance (SPG) dated July 2014, or any successor document, shall comply with the emissions requirements therein.

Condition : 40 - Prior to commencement of superstructure works, a Bird Hazard Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The submitted plan shall include details of:
-Management of any flat/shallow pitched/green roofs on buildings within the site which may be attractive to nesting, roosting and ?loafing? birds. -Confirmation that flat/shallow pitched roofs shall be constructed to allow access to all areas by foot using permanent fixed access stairs ladders or similar and that gulls shall not be allowed to nest, roost or loaf on the building. Checks must be made weekly or sooner if bird activity dictates, during the breeding season. Outside of the breeding season gull activity must be monitored and the roof checked regularly to ensure that gulls do not utilise the roof. Any gulls found nesting, roosting or loafing must be dispersed by the owner/occupier when detected or when requested by Heathrow Airside Operations staff. Any nests or eggs found on the roof shall be removed. Appropriate licenses shall be obtained from Natural England where necessary before the removal of nests and eggs.
The Bird Hazard Management Plan shall be implemented as approved and shall remain in force for the life of the buildings.

Condition : 41 - Prior to commencement of works to the existing river wall, details shall be submitted as outlined in parts a, b and c of this condition below. These details shall be approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, in consultation with the Environment Agency. The proposed measures shall be implemented in accordance with the approved scheme and retained as such permanently thereafter. These details shall include:
a) A scheme of ecological enhancement measures to be incorporated as part of the river wall works. These measures shall include Tiber fenders between MHWN and MHWS and Vertipools. The scheme would also need to demonstrate that an increase of approximately 80m? in foreshore area as outlined in the Second Issue of the document titled ?River Wall Asset Management Strategy? (ref: FNH444-RP-001, dated 25.07.2022). Further details to incorporate new floating reed-bed habitats (subject to navigational requirements); increased mud flat habitat and/or additional planters shall be planted.
b) Details of long-term design objectives, management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all new habitat created as part of part (a) above shall be submitted.
c) A method statement which is to be approved by the Local Planning Authority, in consultation with the Environment Agency demonstrating how The River Brent will be protected during works and shall include the following components:
i. The timing of the works
ii. The measures to be used during the development in order to minimise environmental impact of the works (considering both potential disturbance and pollution)
iii. The ecological enhancements as mitigation for the loss of habitat resulting from the development;
iv. A map or plan showing habitat areas to be specifically protected during the works
v. Any necessary mitigation for protected species
vi. Construction methods
vii. Any necessary pollution protection methods
viii. Information on the persons/bodies responsible for particular activities a

Condition : 42 - Prior to first occupation of Block EFG, details of the balcony treatments shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details shall include plans, elevations and sections to show the means of enclosure and openings of the balconies. Works shall be carried out in accordance with the agreed details and retained as such in perpetuity.

Condition : 43 - Prior to first occupation of the commercial units, a marketing strategy shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The strategy shall include details of marketing to local businesses.
